{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2052","heading":"Requirements","label":"2052 Requirements","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/ptII/ch20/schVI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in Text, referred to in subsec. (d)(2), is set out as a note under .Section 107 of Public Law 102–405section 527 of this title","Amendments2004—Subsec. (c)(1). substituted “services, other commercial activities,” for “services”.Pub. L. 108–4542001—, renumbered as this section.Pub. L. 107–95, § 5(d)(1)section 3773 of this titleSubsec. (a). , substituted “” for “” in introductory provisions.Pub. L. 107–95, § 5(d)(2)(C)section 2051 of this titlesection 3772 of this title","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective , see , set out as an Effective Date of 1998 Amendment note under .Oct. 1, 1998section 602(f) of Pub. L. 105–368section 2106 of this title"],"amendments":["References in Text, referred to in subsec. (d)(2), is set out as a note under .Section 107 of Public Law 102–405section 527 of this title","Amendments2004—Subsec. (c)(1). substituted “services, other commercial activities,” for “services”.Pub. L. 108–4542001—, renumbered as this section.Pub. L. 107–95, § 5(d)(1)section 3773 of this titleSubsec. (a). , substituted “” for “” in introductory provisions.Pub. L. 107–95, § 5(d)(2)(C)section 2051 of this titlesection 3772 of this title","Effective DateSection effective , see , set out as an Effective Date of 1998 Amendment note under .Oct. 1, 1998section 602(f) of Pub. L. 105–368section 2106 of this title"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"construction of, rehabilitation of, or acquisition of land for a multifamily transitional housing project described in subsection (b), or more than one of such purposes; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"refinancing of an existing loan for such a project; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"financing acquisition of furniture, equipment, supplies, or materials for the project; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in the case of a loan made for purposes of subparagraph (A)(i), supplying the organization carrying out the project with working capital relative to the project.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The loan is made in connection with funding or the provision of substantial property or services for such project by either a State or local government or a nongovernmental entity, or both.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that amount generally approved (utilizing prudent underwriting principles) in the consideration and approval of projects of similar nature and risk so as to assure repayment of the loan obligation; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"90 percent of the total cost of the project.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The loan is of sound value, taking into account the creditworthiness of the entity (and the individual members of the entity) applying for such loan.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The loan is secured.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fa%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The loan is subject to such terms and conditions as the Secretary determines are reasonable, taking into account other housing projects with similarities in size, location, population, and services provided.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provides transitional housing to homeless veterans, which housing may be single room occupancy (as defined in section 8(n) of the United States Housing Act of 1937 ( (n)));42 U.S.C. 1437f","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provides supportive services and counselling services (including job counselling) at the project site with the goal of making such veterans self-sufficient;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"requires that each such veteran seek to obtain and maintain employment;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"charges a reasonable fee for occupying a unit in such housing; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"maintains strict guidelines regarding sobriety as a condition of occupying such unit.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":null,"label":"c","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may include space for neighborhood retail services, other commercial activities, or job training programs; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"at the time of taking occupancy by any such veteran or homeless individual, the transitional housing needs of homeless veterans in the project area have been met;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the housing needs of any such veteran or homeless individual can be met in a manner that is compatible with the manner in which the needs of homeless veterans are met under paragraph (1); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the provisions of paragraphs (4) and (5) of subsection (b) are met.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":null,"label":"d","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the availability of Department of Veterans Affairs medical services to residents of the multifamily transitional housing project; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s2052/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs2052%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the extent to which needs of homeless veterans are met in a community, as assessed under .section 107 of Public Law 102–405","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
